climbs.name: We're Going to Need a Bigger Net

content.description:
If you have ever been out fishing in Mills Lacs you will know this is an extremely remote link of lakes. This large granite face rises directly out of the water. At about 50', this free climb can be intimidating, with a drop into water that is anywhere from 10-15 feet deep at the base. This climb is about a 30 minutes boat ride from Pine Point Resort and is very secluded Boat. The only way this climb is accessible is by a 30 minute boat ride from the Pine Point Resort. I would reccommend showing this map to the resort owner of either PPR or Thunderbird Resort on the lake. Deep water if you feel confident enough
Otherwise you can approach from the right and drop a top rope
If you have ever been out fishing in Mills Lacs you will know this is an extremely remote link of lakes. This wall is about 150 yards long that varies in height and slope of the climbs.
